gov.usgs.anss.smprobe

Class UpdateStrongMotion

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.smprobe.UpdateStrongMotion

  • public class UpdateStrongMotion
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains a main method which utilizes the SeedLinkProbe and SeedLinkChannel classes to probe various SeedLink servers for strong motion channels and adds them to the EdgeChannelServer if not already present.

    When run with the -test flag, the database mode us used. The edge.seedlinkserver table then drives this program where each entry with a gaptype in that table will be scanned for channels matching the regular expression on that table from the SeedLink ip/port given. 

     -db=URL             Set the DBServer property to URL for this run, -db only use DBServer property is is
 -emails     list    Set a list of email address to receive the email from each non-zero run (def=ketchum)
 -stasrvip   ip.adr  Set the StaSrv metadata server to this ip address or dns translatable server (cef=cwbpub)
 -stasrvport port    Set the StaSrv metadata server to use this port (def=2052)
 -retrysecs  secs    If non-zero, this program continues to run and does a wait of this many secs between runs(def=0)
 -test               Execute the non-database test code, this is the only thing translated if used.

        Updates the EdgeChannelServer by creating a SeedLinkProbe and checking for strong motion channels with metadata to be included. The method returns an int that designates how many channels were addded to the EdgeChannelSever.
        Parameters:
        server - Address for the SeedLink server to be queried by slinktool.
        port - Numeric port for the SeedLink server.
        ss - Open StaSrv to connect to metadata server.
        mail - The email body string builder
        gapType - String designating channel gaptype. Default is "PW"
        doCount - Boolean flag telling whether or not to count added channels.
        Returns:
        Number of channels added to EdgeChannelServer. -1 if doCount is false.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
